<HEADLINE>
LUCKY BREAK: PENA'S ARM ONLY STRAINED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Los Angeles Dodgers caught a break when Angel
Pena's injured left forearm was diagnosed as a strain by Dr. Frank
Jobe on Monday at Centinela Hospital Medical Center.
</P>
<P>
   Pena, who is listed as day-to-day, was hurt during the brawl
with the Seattle Mariners on Sunday. Since the team is off for
three games because of the All-Star break, Pena could be available
when the Dodgers begin a three-game series Thursday against the
Angels.
</P>
<P>
   The suspensions from the brawl could be announced either today
or Wednesday. Catcher Todd Hundley, reliever Pedro Borbon and coach
Rick Dempsey were all ejected from the game.
</P>
<P>
   The National League will handle the Dodgers' suspensions. The
American League will discipline Seattle's offenders.
</P>
<P>
   __ Osuna gets closer: Rehabbing right-hander Antonio Osuna made
his third appearance with Class-A San Bernardino on Sunday. It was
his first stint as a reliever. Osuna allowed three hits in two
shutout innings, walking one and striking out three.
</P>
<P>
   Osuna, recovering from the removal of a bone spur in his
pitching elbow, is scheduled to pitch today. If all goes well, he's
expected to be activated Thursday. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
