<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Video games by the numbers
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   _ There are 3.5 million serious gamers in this country. On
average, each of these avid hobbyists spends $720 a year on video
games, buys 20 games a year and spends $2,500 every two years to
upgrade his or her computer.
</P>
<P>
   _ A larger audience of gamers includes 20 million who play some
kind of game every now and then.
</P>
<P>
   _ More than 90 percent of computer games are purchased by people
older than 18.
</P>
<P>
   _ Game consoles, including the PlayStation and the Nintendo 64,
account for about three-quarters of the gaming industry.
</P>
<P>
   Source: Computer Gaming World magazine
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
