   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ With each day comes new protests in
Yugoslavian towns. The protesters want Slobodan Milosovic removed
from office. While that may be comforting to the U.S. State
Department and NATO, I find something quite discomforting about it.
The protesters seem to want Milosovic removed for the wrong reason.
(Howard Kleinberg is a columnist for Cox News Service.). 17. MOVED
MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ My good friend Gail _ the
one who moved to the Oregon coast a few years back with little more
than a basket of books and a featherbed _ has had a bit of bad
luck. Seems she lost her most recent beau to an Internet
seductress. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ PARIS _ There is a love story being written
here at every turn. But it is not simply lovers embraced on park
benches. It is more than that. All of Paris is in love. All of
Paris is in love with Paris. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ I'll miss the national debt. It was
something you could count on. (Rosenfeld, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ Readers who missed the news that Bush had already
won the presidency can be excused for being disoriented. This time,
rather than use the traditional means of electing a president,
we've gone to the auction-barn method. And bids apparently have
closed. Sold, to G.W. Bush. But Bush's money edge _ more than an
edge, this is the continental shelf _ is already winnowing the GOP
field. (Young, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ALLAN-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ If you're a klutz around the house
and yard, Chuck and Jay say thanks. And keep up the bad work. I
