   VIDEOGAMES-VIOLENCE _ The killings at Columbine High School
prompted lawsuits against the makers of Doom, the granddaddy of
violent video games, but Doom looks like child's play compared to
the games that are out now, including Kingpin, just released last
week, which allows you to form your own mafia (not the trenchcoat
kind) shoot your victim in 15 different body parts. A look at
violoent video games, and those who play them. Photo tba. art from
boxes of games, frame grabs available. (Emerson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 60. MOVED.
