   SURGEON-GENERAL (Albany, N.Y.) _ Dr. Antonia Novello, the former
U.S. Surgeon General and the new New York state health
commissioner, seem to be hitting her stride, meeting with many of
the department's 7,000 employees and visiting regional offices.
Staffers praised the commissioner's approachability and her efforts
to reach out to the rank and file. By PAUL GRONDAHL.
</P>
<P>
   BOTTLE-RECYCLING (Albany, N.Y.) _ While New Yorkers are
recycling a hefty 42 percent of all trash, the rate is nearly
double for bottles and cans sold with nickel deposits. Still, well
over a billion beverage containers _ one out of four sold _ are
never cashed in and the money stays with the distributors. By DINA
CAPPIELLO.
