<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`LITTLE HOUSE' HAD A FEW ADDITIONS AFTER LANDON DIED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Were any segments of ``Little House on the Prairie''
made after Michael Landon's death?
</P>
<P>
   _ R.M., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ The last TV project related to the series was the 1984
TV movie ``Bless All the Little Children,'' which aired seven years
before Landon died of cancer in 1991.
</P>
<P>
   The movie was the third after the end of the ``Little House on
the Prairie'' TV series in 1983. The first two were ``Little House:
Look Back to Yesterday'' and ``Little House: The Last Farewell.''
</P>
<P>
   A CBS movie, ``Beyond the Prairie: The True Story of Laura
Ingalls Wilder,'' has been filmed but not aired. It stars Meridith
Monroe, Richard Thomas and Lindsey Crouse.
</P>
<P>
   There may be a big-screen version in the works: A 1997 news
report indicated that Horton Foote had been signed to write a
screenplay.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ My grandmother, a big Chicago Cubs fan, turns 95 in
August. How can I contact someone to send a birthday card or
autographed picture of the team?
</P>
<P>
   _ F.Y., Everman, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ Send your request to the Chicago Cubs, Community
Relations Dept., 1060 W. Addision St., Chicago, Ill. 60613.
</P>
<P>
   The same address can be used to write Sammy Sosa, Mark Grace and
other members of the team; address letters to the specific player
you want to contact. The Cubs also have a World Wide Web site at
www.chicagocubs.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
