<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  
 July 13, 1999   Editors:  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Newspapers that published BC-MEANS-COLUMN filed Monday, July 12,
on the Hearst News Service may wish to use the following
corrective:
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ A Marianne Means column about female athletics
incorrectly identified the portion of the federal law requiring
equal treatment of male and female athletics in educational
institutions receiving federal funding. It is Title IX.
</P>
