 Attn Sports Editors:  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sports stories from The New York Times News Service for
Wednesday, July 14.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-ANDERSON-COLUMN (Boston) _ Sports column on the All-Star
Game. By Dave Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-ALLSTAR-GAME (Boston) _ Lede-all on The All-Star Game, 8:15
p.m. The early story will focus on the non-stars who have replaced
some very familiar names. For instance, the National League
pitching staff does not include Greg Maddux and Tom Glavine but
does have Paul Byrd, Jose Lima and Kent Bottenfield. By Murray
Chass.
</P>
<P>
   Sidebars as warranted.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-BRITISH-OPEN (Carnoustie, Scotland) _ British Open feature
focusing on Tiger Woods, who is playing as consistently as he ever
has since turning pro and would seem to have a good shot at winning
this weekend. By Clifton Brown.
</P>
<P>
   TOURDEFRANCE (Sestrieres, Italy) _ Lance Armstrong took a huge
step toward victory in the Tour de France Tuesday by surging ahead
of his rivals on the tough first mountain stage and keeping a firm
hold on first place. By Samuel Abt.
</P>
<P>
   BKW-WNBA (New York) _ Advance on the WNBA All-Star game, which
takes place Wednesday night at a sold-out Madison Square Garden.
Story will focus on some of the less-familiar names in the game. By
Jerry Brewer.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
