<P>
   AUSTIN-ECONOMY _ WASHINGTON _ Austin has the reputation as
Texas's high-tech heaven, but Dallas has the mojo. A new study
measuring the impact of new technologies on regional economies
shows that metro Dallas is second only to the Silicon Valley for
being a tech mega-center. Austin-San Marcos turns up as No. 21 on a
list of 315 cities studied. But an economist who helped prepare the
study, Perry Wong, says Austin's place among the Top 25 tech
centers may be more precarious that city boosters may believe, and
that Dallas is more firmly entrenched. That's because Dallas has a
very complex technology base, with seven different high-tech
industries represented. Austin, in contrast, has a lot of high-tech
jobs, but they are highly concentrated in the business of making
computers. (Geewax, Cox News Service). 25.
