   LAST-CODE (Half Moon Bay, Calif.) _ Archaic in an era of
dot.coms, the finals dots and dashes of commercial telegraph were
transmitted by a California company Monday night. The telegraph
station at Half Moon Bay and three others were the last in North
America to broadcast ship-to-shore messages by Morse code. The
final transmission was the same one Samuel F.B. Morse, inventor of
the telegraph, used in the first message he sent in 1844: ``What
hath God wrought?'' By ZACHARY COILE.
