</P>
<P>
   VALUJET-INDICTMENT (Dateline to be determined) _ A federal grand
jury investigating the 1996 crash of ValuJet Flight 592 has
indicted the airline's maintenance contractor and some of its
employees on murder and manslaughter charges. It is believed to be
the first time in U.S. aviation history that criminal charges were
filed against maintenance workers after an airplane crash.
Investigators found that workers for the contractor, SabreTech
Inc., improperly packed oxygen canisters that were loaded into the
jetliner's cargo hold, where a fire caused the DC-9 to plunge into
the Everglades on May 11, 1996, killing all 110 on board. (Summary
from wires.) By Matthew L. Wald.
</P>
