   SPRAWL (Salt Lake City) _ Special report: The Salt Lake
metropolitan area is growing by 1,000 acres a month, much of it to
the alarm of Utah's political and business leaders. But in a blitz
of highway construction the state's leaders are encouraging the
very thing they say they do not want: instant towns in a sea of
pavement and brown air. But in Milwaukee officials plan to use more
than $20 million in federal transportation money to tear down a
half-built section of highway that was supposed to cut right
through old Milwaukee. The two cities are using federal
transportation subsidies to go in opposite directions _ Salt Lake
to speed people into and out of the city, Milwaukee to revive city
life. By Timothy Egan.
</P>
