<P>
   COLORADO-JUDGE-ALLARD. Sen. Wayne Allard's chief of staff met
with White House staff to discuss Allard's suggestions for a spot
on the federal bench in Denver. Last month, Allard blocked
President Clinton's nomination of Patricia Coan. (500 words.) By
Sara Kugler
</P>
<P>
   COLORADO-FARM. Colorado's farmers and ranchers are suffering the
same economic woes that the rest of the nation's agriculture
industry is facing, according to the president of the Colorado Farm
Bureau. If Congress doesn't lend a hand, he says, the results will
be devastating to Colorado. (600 words.) By Sara Kugler
</P>
<P>
   CONNECTICUT-HMO-SENATE. Connecticut Senators have been embroiled
this week in the tangled debate on the Republican HMO bill,
introducing several amendments to the legislation. A look at what
they are seeking. (500 words.) By Jill Carroll
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA-JUDGES. Florida's Senators on Tuesday pushed for
nominees to fill key federal judgeships in the state. (250 words.)
By Sean Gorman
</P>
<P>
   MAINE-HEAT. Both President Clinton and cooler temperatures are
bringing relief to areas hard hit by last week's heat wave. Clinton
released $100 million yesterday to help low-income families in
sixteen states in New England, the mid-Atlantic region and the
Midwest. Maine will receive $782,566. (500 words.) By Laura Rodini
</P>
<P>
   MASSACHUSETTS-COOL-AID. Massachusetts is one of 17 states that
will receive emergency federal funds to help poor residents cope
with hot weather. (320 words.) By C.J. Karamargin
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-OIL. The American Petroleum Institute, a Washington-based
trade association that represents the nation's major companies,
said it opposes the anti-dumping petition filed by a group of
independent oil producers with the Commerce Department and the
International Trade Commission. (400 words.) By Robin Brown
</P>
<P>
   LOUISIANNA-FTC-SECURITY. The Federal Trade Commission is
recommending Internet self-regulation on consumer safety involving
personal information such as credit card numbers. (600 words.) By
Matt Swenson
</P>
<P>
   MULTICHANNEL-FTC-SECURITY. The FTC is recommending Internet
self-regulation on consumer safety involving personal information
such as credit card numbers. (600 words.) By Matt Swenson
</P>
