<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; QUICKIE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Upon returning to their car from a shopping tour, one of the
young ladies realized that she had forgotten to stop at the
pharmacy for her birth control pills. She rushed into the nearest
pharmacy and gave her prescription to the pharmacist.
</P>
<P>
   `Please fill this immediately,` she asked. `I've got people
waiting in my
</P>
<P>
   car!`
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINAL EXAM &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The not necessarily well-prepared student sat in his life
science classroom staring at a question on the final exam paper.
The question directed: `Give four advantages of breast milk.` What
to write? He sighed, and began to scribble whatever came into his
head, hoping for the best:
</P>
<P>
   1. No need to boil.
</P>
<P>
   2. Cats can't steal it.
</P>
<P>
   3. Available whenever necessary.
</P>
<P>
   So far so good - maybe. But the exam demanded a four-part
answer. Again, what to write? Once more, he sighed. He frowned. He
scowled, then sighed again. But suddenly, he brightened. He grabbed
his pen, and triumphantly, he scribbled his definitive answer:
</P>
<P>
   4. Available in attractive containers.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OPENING REMARKS FROM THE ``LATE SHOW with DAVID LETTERMAN'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Listen to how hot it was earlier today -- I'm not making this
up, this was true. Earlier today, a guy, a fat guy, falls asleep on
a waterbed, it's so hot he wakes up with a hard-boiled ass.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Boy, you can tell it's summer in New York! Here's what
happened last night -- they found a naked dead guy in the tank at
Red Lobster.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Last night, my bug zapper, honest to God, dropped more flies
than a White House intern.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not only hot here in New York City, it's hot down there
in Washington, D.C. It was so hot earlier today, President Clinton
dropped his pants in front of an air conditioner.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It was so hot in the White House, President Clinton was
staying very, very close to Hillary -- just for the chill.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It was so hot in the Oval Office, interns were crawling under
Clinton's desk just for the shade.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Boris Yeltsin has announced that next year he's going to
resign, step down as President of Russia. He's going to take a
couple of months off and he's going to run for Senate from New
York.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's so hot today, Hillary Clinton has changed her mind, she's
going to run for the Senate from Maine.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Big news yesterday in New York. Here in Manhattan, we had the
power blackouts -- lost power because of the heat and the city went
black. It was awful, down there at Dunkin' Donuts, the power went
off -- the mice were eating dinner by candlelight.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Hillary Clinton this week is kicking off her listening
tour.'She's traveling around the state of New York listening.'
Here's what she should have been doing: she should have been
listening outside the Oval Office.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we're all very excited here in New York because
Hillary has started her four-day statewide New York listening
tour'...And right after that she'll begin her illegal fundraising
tour.''
</P>
<P>
   This listening tour,' I'm baffled by this, I just don't get it.
What is the point, the listening tour?' I mean, my God, after being
married to Clinton, you think she'd heard it all.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Hillary Clinton's running for Senate...This is an historic
moment for Hillary Clinton. This is their first step toward the
Clintons becoming a two-impeachment family.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Of course, you know Hillary Clinton is in New York State now
on her listening tour.' The campaign is all starting to come
together: she's on the listening tour now, she's raising funds,
next week she's hiring male interns.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I think honestly Hillary is starting to feel more at ease with
New Yorkers because she opened up a campaign speech earlier today
by doing a couple of jokes about Monica Lewinsky.''
</P>
<P>
   ``This listening tour, she's driving around New York State
listening to the voters...And the voters are all telling Hillary,
Go back to Arkansas!'''
</P>
<P>
   ``You know, they're playing another one of those interleague
deals, Subway Series,' the Yankees and the Mets...Everybody asking
Hillary, Who do you prefer, the Yankees or the Mets?'...It's not a
fair question to ask Hillary. That's like asking Bill, Who's your
favorite Jane Doe?'''
</P>
<P>
   ``Bill and Hillary are coming to New York City so she can run
for Senate. They've already got a house picked out and the rent for
this house is $20,000 damn dollars...Bill and Hillary are on a
budget, they only can afford to spend $10,000 a month. They're not
worried because Hillary's sure she can make up the difference with
a crooked real estate deal.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The Clintons don't want to spend more than $10,000 a month on
their new home. Keep something in mind, folks -- this is the same
couple that was charging $50,000 a night to sleep in the Lincoln
Bedroom.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Say what you will about Bill Clinton, he's a very simple guy
when it comes to housing. Really, if you think about it, all he
wants, all he needs is a roof over his head and an intern under his
desk.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Meanwhile, President Clinton, her husband, he's on a poverty
tour, and earlier today or yesterday, he stopped at a Sioux
reservation in North Dakota. It's interesting, the Sioux have kind
of a cute nickname for President Clinton -- they call him Chief
Crazypants.'''
</P>
