<P>
   COKE-SUIT _ ATLANTA _ The gloves come off Thursday. That's when
lawyers for Coca-Cola and the four plaintiffs suing the company for
racial discrimination will argue over a key part of the case _
whether to eliminate the possibility of it becoming a
``class-action'' suit in the future. If it becomes a class-action
case down the road, the plaintiffs could potentially represent
1,500 other salaried Coke employees in the United States. (Unger,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TECH-SMALLBIZ _ Definition 6, an Atlanta-based interactive
advertising and marketing company, hopes to capture the small
business market with a promotion called Websiteforfree.com. The
company joins such heavyweights as BellSouth, MindSpring and IBM in
the race to capture the online small business market. (Katz,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   SMALLBIZ-TIPS _ Tips from experts on what to do and avoid when
looking to build your own online store. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SLATE-CHANGES _ Slate has always been notorious for keeping its
light under a bushel and in the shadow of that other popular online
magazine, Salon. But now it seems that Slate may have finally found
a combination of editorial, commerce and alternative revenue
streams to push the Microsoft-owned site into mainstream acceptance
after three years of failed attempts. Monday, in the Web site's
daily e-mail ``morning delivery,'' there was a note from famed
editor Michael Kinsley talking up Slate's latest efforts aimed at
reaching a broader audience and tapping into current Web trends.
The new and improved Slate has taken a huge leap into the next
century with versions now available for PalmPilot and Windows CE
users. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is the CoxNet WHEELS page for the current week. This
layout is now available.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS 0710: 1999 CHEVROLET SILVERADO _ The 10th
anniversary special edition of the MX-5 Miata clearly isn't for
everyone who wants a two-seater because of its inflated price. But
it does stand out in a niche market segment catering to traditional
sports car enthusiasts. (DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art
includes 3-column color photo of car's exterior and an 6-pica color
photo of car's interior.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   AT A GLANCE _ Fact box previewing the 1999 Miata 10th
anniversary edition.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP DRIVING _ Whether you are making an out-of-state car trip
or just a short ride to a nearby lake or mountain retreat, don't
spoil your summer vacation by letting the heat and the boil of
traffic get the best of you. (Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
Includes 1-column color photograph of columnist.
</P>
<P>
   END OF PAGE
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ A review of the new Saturn midsize L-Series.
(Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TESTDRIVE-IMPALA _ A test drive of the 2000 Chevrolet Impala
(DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ Readers often ask what books would help them get
smart about investing in general and the stock market in
particular. That's no surprise. A lot more people have investments
these days because they have 401(k) retirement plans. Others have
gotten interested because they keep hearing about the booming stock
market. Publishers know this hunger exists. That's why there are so
many investment advice books in the stores and libraries. Some of
those books are very good. But some are them are awful. We list
some good places to start. (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
