<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   VALUJET-INDICT _ MIAMI _ A federal grand jury today is expected
to indict the air maintenance company that packed more than 140
flammable oxygen-generating canisters later placed on ValuJet
Airlines Flight 592, which slammed into the Everglades moments
after takeoff in 1996, killing all 110 aboard. Critics have charged
that, three years later, many dramatic changes promised in the wake
of the crash have died aborning. (Kleinberg, Palm Beach Post). 40.
</P>
<P>
   w/VALUJET-BOX _ MIAMI _ Highlights of the indictment.
(Kleinberg, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   VALUJET-TIME _ MIAMI _ VlauJet crash/investigation chronology.
(Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   MASSACRE-FOLO _ATLANTA _ Follow on Monday's seven-person
shooting in southwest Atlanta. Update police investigation; look at
history of police calls to the house at 3783 Adamsville Drive; try
to learn more about what the 11-year-old survivor saw and how he
escaped into a closet; funeral planning for seven; more community
react; why did the police wait three hours to get into the house
when someone could have been alive inside? (Longa, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   RAIL-KILLER _ Rafael Resendez-Ramirez, the train-riding fugitive
suspected of killing eight people who lived near railroad tracks,
surrendered at a border checkpoint in El Paso, Texas today in a
deal brokered by his sister.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: American-Statesman reporters will be filing from Austin,
Houston and El Paso for this story.
</P>
<P>
   SKOLSHOOT-HEARING _ ATLANTA _ Anthony ``T.J.'' Solomon, accused
in the shooting last May at Heritage High School in Rockdale
County, Ga., has a hearing Tuesday on whether he should be tried as
an adult. (Stafford, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   CUBA (DEVELOPING) _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ It's summer and time
for the annual exodus from Cuba, as immigrants take advantage of
calm seas to reach the U.S. shores. Rafters seem more desperate to
reach the ground, we find out why. (Douthat, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON _ MIAMI _ President Clinton is visiting Miami to attend
a political fundraiser. (Crowley, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
