   PIPELINE (Seattle) _ An inspection of the 400-mile Olympic
pipeline turned up hundreds of potential problems three years ago,
forcing workers to dig up and repair or even replace some sections.
But Olympic Pipe Line Co. decided none of the problems in and
around Bellingham, Wash., merited special attention even though 19
anomalies were found. It was that section of pipe that ruptured
