Committee, duiring a news conference about his tax cut proposals on
Tuesday. The House Ways and Means Committee took the first step on
Tuesday toward a partisan showdown over how to allocate the
projected Federal budget surplus, opening debate on a Republican
proposal to send $864 billion back to taxpayers over the next
decade. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
</P>
