terracotta sculpture by Benedetto Pietromarchi lays in pieces after
being vandalized during an exhibition at a Rome cemetery. ``I am
very sorry that this happened,'' says Carmine Sorrentino, one of
the show's curators, after several works of art were destroyed.
``The exhibition was meant to be a reflection on death and
contemporary art, and we didn't mean to offend anyone or do
anything that would be upsetting. But we cannot continue after
this.'' (James Hill/New York Times Photo)
</P>
