Le Cirque 2000, melon is served with a glass of port. With the
simplest embellishment, a slice of melon can be transformed into a
light dessert or refreshing first course. (Philip Greenberg/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) NEW YORK -- July 13, 1999 -- SUMMER-MELON-1, 07-13 --
Watermelon blends with calamari and avocado at Union Pacific.
Melons are the aristocrats of summer fruit, their cool elegance and
exotic lushness perfuming dishes with the fragrances of a flower
garden. (Philip Greenberg/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
