highways. Two thousand workers are pouring concrete around the
clock, turning six lanes of Interstate 15 into 12 lanes through
Salt Lake City and its loping suburbs. Salt Lake City and
Milwaukee, two cities with roughly equal metropolitan populations
(about 1.5 million), each having declared war on urban sprawl, are
examples of how federal transportation subsidies are still one of
the biggest forces shaping urban areas .(Tom Smart/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT8) NEW YORK -- July 13, 1999 -- SOCCER-HEROES , 07-13 -- The
