M.S. Ecstasy leaves Miami in December 1998. A report released on
Tuesday reveals the extent of alleged sexual assaults that occured
on the company's cruise ships. (Paul Hosefros/New york Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) ROME -- July 13, 1999 -- ITALY-CEMETERY-2, 07-13 -- A
terracotta sculpture by Benedetto Pietromarchi lays in pieces after
being vandalized during an exhibition at a Rome cemetery. ``I am
very sorry that this happened,'' says Carmine Sorrentino, one of
the show's curators, after several works of art were destroyed.
``The exhibition was meant to be a reflection on death and
contemporary art, and we didn't mean to offend anyone or do
anything that would be upsetting. But we cannot continue after
this.'' (James Hill/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) ROME -- July 13, 1999 -- ITALY-CEMETERY, 07-13 --
Prominent English speakers in Rome opposed a show in a cemetery
where John Keats, tombstone at left, is buried. ``I am very sorry
that this happened,'' says Carmine Sorrentino, one of the show's
curators, after several works of art were vandalized. ``The
exhibition was meant to be a reflection on death and contemporary
art, and we didn't mean to offend anyone or do anything that would
be upsetting. But we cannot continue after this.'' (James Hill/New
York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) WANTAGH, N.Y. -- July 13, 1999 -- MRS-CLINTON, 07-13 --
Hillary Rodham Clinton poses for a photo with beachgoers at Jones
Beach on Tuesday. It wasn't Ricky Martin or even gorgeous weather
that drew a cheering crowd of several hundred Tuesday to the beach.
It was an impromptu stop on Hillary Rodham Clinton's listening
tour. (Keith Meyers/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) MILWAUKEE -- July13, 1999 -- SPRAWL-4, 07-13 -- Mayor
John Norquist stands on a corner of Water Street near the Park East
Freeway. The elevated highway was built by the state of Wisconsin
using federal funds. ``The urban superhighway should be relegated
to the scrap heap of history,'' says Norquist, Milwaukee's
three-term mayor, who toured the country recently to make his case
that cities should be removing highways, not building new ones.
(Todd Buchanan/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) UNDATED -- July 13, 1999 -- SUMMER-MELON-3, 07-13 -- A
variety of melons, whether from local farms, from California or
