INDONESIA-COOKING-OIL, 07-13 -- A Javanese man walks to his home
after a day working in the rice fields in late June. Farmers like
these make up the huge majority of Indonesia's population of more
than 200 million, and a huge majority of its electorate. Yet most
of the country's hot political issues -- corruption, democracy, the
role of the military -- are little more than words for many of
them. (Paula Bronstein/New York Times Photo) LITE
