<P>
   BC-OBIT-RAMIREZ-NYT (moved on Monday, July 12)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Carlos D. Ramirez, sent by the New York Times
News Service on Monday, July 12, carried an erroneous byline. It
was by Nick Ravo.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SIXTY-MINUTES-MOVIE-NYT (moved on Monday, July 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, July 12,
about ``The Insider,'' a film drama based on CBS's refusal to
broadcast a ``60 Minutes'' interview with a tobacco company
whistle-blower, misstated the year a tobacco executive died. Thomas
E. Sandefur Jr. of Brown &AMP; Williamson who testified before Congress
about tobacco's addictive properties, died in 1996, not 1966.
</P>
