   HMOS-SERVICES (Undated) _ Investor-owned HMOs are significantly
more likely to skimp on medical services, including mammograms,
post-heart-attack treatments and immunizations, than nonproft HMOs.
By Richard Saltus. 700 words. (a and f coding)
</P>
